------------------[ FEROX COMMANDS ]------------------

  Core Commands:
    help, ?  ->  Show this help message
    help scanners  ->  Show available scanner modules
    help exploits  ->  Show available exploit modules
    help sessions  ->  Show session management help
    modules, list, ls  ->  List all available modules
    use <module>  ->  Select a module to use
    back  ->  Deselect current module

  Module Commands:
    show <type>  ->  Show information (options, modules, sessions)
    set <option> <value>, s  ->  Set module option
    options, o  ->  Show current module options
    check, c  ->  Run non-destructive check (safe fingerprinting)
    run, execute, x, e  ->  Execute current module
    info, i  ->  Show current module information

  Session Commands:
    sessions  ->  List all sessions
    sessions -a  ->  List active sessions only
    sessions -i <id>  ->  Show session details
    sessions -k <id>  ->  Mark session inactive
    sessions -r <id>  ->  Remove session
    sessions -c <hours>  ->  Cleanup stale sessions

  Handler Commands:
    handlers  ->  List all registered handlers
    handlers -s  ->  Show handler statistics
    handlers -k <id>  ->  Remove handler by ID
    handlers -t <type>  ->  List handlers by type

  Shell & Execution:
    shell  ->  Create new local shell handler
    shell -i <id>  ->  Select existing shell handler
    exec <command>  ->  Execute command in current shell
    sysinfo  ->  Display system information
    ps  ->  List running processes
    kill <pid>  ->  Terminate process by PID

  File Operations:
    upload <src> <dst>  ->  Upload file to target
    download <src> <dst>  ->  Download file from target
    pwd  ->  Print current working directory
    cd <path>  ->  Change working directory
    cat <file>  ->  Display file contents
    rm <file>  ->  Delete file
    mkdir <dir>  ->  Create directory

  Remote Shell:
    listen <port>  ->  Start reverse shell listener
    connect <host> <port>  ->  Create bind shell connection

  Report & Export Commands:
    export <format> <file>  ->  Export results (json, html, pdf)
    export results  ->  Show stored results summary

  Utility Commands:
    banner  ->  Display Ferox banner
    version  ->  Show version information
    payloads  ->  List available payload blueprints
    clear, cls  ->  Clear the screen
    exit, quit, q  ->  Exit the framework

  💡 Tip:
    Use TAB for command completion. Type 'help <category>' for focused help.

  ⚠️  Safety Notice:
    Always use 'check' before 'run' for exploit modules
    Exploits require explicit confirmation
    Only test systems you own or have permission to test

